#{{compsci}} A macro is an [[abstraction]] whereby a certain textual pattern is replaced according to a defined set of rules.
#{{complang}} The name of a specific textual pattern taken in the context of a specific set of replacement rules -- a name (possibly followed by a formal argument list) that is equated to a body of text (possibly including notation marking the placement of arguments) which [[macro expansion]] substitutes for all occurences of the name (and any arguments) that appear in a second text, the text undergoing macro expansion.
#{{computing}} Any substitution of a collection of actions for a single action.

